headline: Home Depot Stock Edges Lower After Company Provides Muted Outlook
summary: Home Depot shares inched 0.8% lower after the company forecast lower-than-expected sales growth for next year amid an extended downturn in home-improvement activity.  Home Depot predicted same-store sales for fiscal 2026 to grow in the range of flat to 2%, also below analysts’ expectations.  Economic uncertainty and a stalled housing market have made homeowners more cautious about taking on big renovation projects.

headline: Home Depot Shares Fall as Retailer Gives Guarded Fiscal 2026 Forecast
summary: Home Depot  gave a cautious outlook for fiscal 2026 as the housing market continues to lag.  The company also guided for earnings per share to range between flat to up 4% and for comparable-sales growth of flat to up 2%.  Home Depot said it expects those metrics to rise at a faster clip if the housing market gains momentum and there is increased spend on larger projects, driven by pent-up demand.
